                <locus target="#138v" facs="145"/>
                  <q>“This book was copied in 1956 EC in the reign of Hayle Selassie, King of Kings of Ethiopia, in the year of Matthew, the Evangelist.
                  The scribe is poor and destitute, Bǝrhani Abadi of Axum. Copied from a book of Axum Ṣǝyon church.”</q>
                  Added in later hand: <q>“for your servant Kinä Śelassie</q> [i.e., Nǝburä ‘Ǝdǝ Dǝmeṭǝros Gäbrä Maryam]
